<TITLE> Garment workers block traffic to demand wages </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com) - Garments workers blocked Kazi Nazrul Islam Avenue in Karwan Bazar Friday morning, demanding arrears pay, allowances and festival bonuses, police said. The demonstration disrupted traffic on the road for half an hour from 8am, witnesses said. Tejgaon police sub-inspector Hafizur Rahman told bdnews24.com: "Workers of Nahar Garments staged the demonstration." Tejgaon police chief Lutfar Rahman said: "The police persuaded the demonstrators to move away from the main avenue. Efforts are underway to hold meetings between the workers and factory owners to resolve the issue." bdnews24.com/
